The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate. The letter discusses the continuation of a national emergency with respect to terrorists who threaten to disrupt the Middle East peace process. The President states that the crisis involving acts of violence by foreign terrorists has not been resolved, and these actions continue to pose a threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. Therefore, the President determines it is necessary to continue the national emergency and maintain sanctions against these terrorists.